    (function () {
        var s = document.createElement('script'); s.async = true;
        s.type = 'text/javascript';
        s.src = '//' + disqus_shortname + '.disqus.com/count.js';
        (document.getElementsByTagName('HEAD')[0] || document.getElementsByTagName('BODY')[0]).appendChild(s);
    }());
</script></aside><h2><a href="lesson-108-urdu-consonants-part-1-be">Lesson #108: Urdu Consonants Part 1; ب be</a></h2><div class="caption clearfix rte"><p>So what did we learn <a href="../3533177716/lesson-95-urdu-vowels-part-2-i-and-ee">last time</a>&nbsp;we looked at Urdu? That&rsquo;s right, we learnt all about two more Urduvowels, which were&nbsp;<em>i</em> and <em>ee. </em>We also learnt another letter of the Urdu alphabet, <big><big><big>&#1740;</big></big></big> <em>chotee ye</em> - Small Y. If you&rsquo;ve forgotten anything (and I do admit it was quite a while ago!) then head back over to&nbsp;<a href="../3533177716/lesson-95-urdu-vowels-part-2-i-and-ee">Urdu Vowels Part 2</a>&nbsp;and revise over what we did!&nbsp;In today&rsquo;s lesson we&rsquo;re going to learn just one more Urdu consonant! (How easy can you get, hey!).&nbsp;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkqsdkp2rf1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrt1twRzy1qzfx8l.jpg"><em>bandar - </em>Monkey</p><p>By the end of this lesson you should be able to recognize the first letter in this word! (Don&rsquo;t worry about all the other letters for now, we&rsquo;ll get there eventually!)</p><p>So are you ready to get straight into it?</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkqsby19601qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>be&nbsp;</em></p><p>This is the letter we&rsquo;re going to look at today.&nbsp;This is the letter<big><big> &#1576; </big></big><em>be </em>(Rhymes with &lsquo;hey&rsquo;), it makes a normal 'b&rsquo; sound just like the english b in boat. And this letter looks a little bit like a boat don&rsquo;t you think? There&rsquo;s also something very important to note - it has one dot underneath it! This letter is 'equivalent&rsquo; to the Hindi <big><big>&#2348;</big></big> <em>ba.</em></p><p>Now can you remember back to <a href="../2377245694/lesson-82-an-introduction-to-the-urdu-alphabet">An Introduction to the Urdu Alphabet</a>&nbsp;I said that each letter has different 'forms&rsquo; and takes a slightly different shape depending on where it is in the a word. <em>be</em> is no different, so we have to learn how it&rsquo;s shape changes! When it&rsquo;s in the middle or at the start of a word, it gets a little squashed, so for example&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrt4inNeD1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>baagh</em> - Garden&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrsrrAl9Q1qzfx8l.jpg"></p><p>Can you see the one dot underneath the first letter of the word? (Remember we start on the right and read to the left!) That&rsquo;s the squashed up&nbsp;<em>be</em>! It just looks like a little hook with a dot underneath, easy! Whenever <em>be</em> is at the start of a word it must take this little hook shape!</p><p>Hopefully you remember from <a href="../2571682699/lesson-86-urdu-vowels-part-1-a-and-aa">Urdu Vowels Part 1</a> that the little dash above the <em>be </em>follow by an alif means we pronounce it <em>baa</em>. Don&rsquo;t worry if you&rsquo;re confused about the last letter of this word for now we&rsquo;ll learn about it later!</p><p>So how does <em>be</em> look in the middle of a word? Well it actually looks very similar to how it does at the start! So for example&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkqsprnjJM1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp; &nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrtca97i71qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>akhbaar</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;- Newspaper</p><p>Can you see the little hook and the one dot underneath? That&rsquo;s the <em>be</em> again! You should also be able to spot the alif after again too. Whenever <em>be</em> is in the middle of a word it must take this hook shape!&nbsp;</p><p>One more word then, this time we&rsquo;ll have <em>be</em> at the end. When it&rsquo;s at the end of a word <em>be</em> stretches back out to normal again, like in the Urdu word&hellip;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrtug0O7B1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>kab</em>&nbsp;&nbsp;- When &nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkqtchuYpj1qzfx8l.jpg"></p><p>Can you see now that the&nbsp;<em>be </em>at the end isn&rsquo;t just a little hook - it&rsquo;s the big boat shape again? Whenever <em>be</em> is at the end it must take this boat shape!&nbsp;</p><p>Are you starting to get the hang of this? Make sure you have a good look at each word as we go through them, it&rsquo;s important for you to see the shape of the letter each time! Ready for some more examples? &nbsp;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrtyx0JRm1qzfx8l.png">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrtzarzFa1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>baithnaa</em> - To Sit</p><p>This words a little more complicated but all you need to focus on is the first letter. Can you see the little hook with a dot underneath at the start? That&rsquo;s our&nbsp;<em>be</em>!</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrv2t5JKS1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>caabee</em> - Key<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrui2hWQr1qzfx8l.jpg"></p><p>(Note 'c&rsquo; is pronounced 'ch&rsquo; like in church). Woah, ok so whats happened here? There&rsquo;s no little hook? Well can you see the one dot underneath in the middle of the word? That&rsquo;s our <em>be</em>! But because it comes after an <em>alif </em>it doesn&rsquo;t join on to the previous part (Remember an<em> alif</em> never joins to the next letter!) and because it comes before a <em>chotee ye </em>the <em>be </em>sits above the line. All you need to notice is the dot underneath!&nbsp;</p><p class="center"><img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrus220qO1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrv49EMT01qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;<em>taaalaab</em> - Pond</p><p>Can you spot the <em>be</em> this time? That&rsquo;s right, it&rsquo;s just sitting at the end, and because it&rsquo;s at the end it&rsquo;s back to the boat shape!</p><p>Do you think you&rsquo;ve understood this lesson? If you have any questions then please feel free to ask me in the comments section below!&nbsp;Do you think you&rsquo;re ready to spot the letter&nbsp;<em>be</em>&nbsp;in some words? Just below are five Urdu words, I want you to see if you can spot the letter <em>be</em> in each of them. If you get stuck be sure to leave me a comment below!</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;1. &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrv0kqaXk1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;&nbsp;- Child &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrv6tB6I41qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;&nbsp;- Language&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 3.&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrvalbYbw1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;&nbsp;- Ill &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 4.&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrvezWXi91qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;&nbsp;- Student</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 5.&nbsp;<img alt="image" src="http://78.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_lkrvnsWTir1qzfx8l.jpg">&nbsp;- Sometime</p><p>Did you spot a <em>be</em> in each of those words? Some of them are harder than others. Leave a comment if you&rsquo;re confused and I&rsquo;ll do my best to help you!</p><p>So well done for reaching the end of this lessons, there&rsquo;s been a lot of crazy letters that we haven&rsquo;t met yet, but unfortunately you have to start somewhere. Next time we&rsquo;re going to look a few more Consonants - but you may be surprised, they&rsquo;ll be a lot easier than you think!</p><p><a href="http://learninghindi.tumblr.com/urdu">Back to the Urdu Section</a>.</p></div><aside class="post-footer"><div class="tags"><span>Tags:</span><a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/letter">letter</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/consonants">consonants</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/be">be</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/nastaliq">nastaliq</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/may2011">may2011</a> <a href="http://www.learning-hindi.com/tagged/urdu">urdu</a> </div><div class="bottom"><div class="like_button" data-post-id="5241958541" data-blog-name="learninghindi" id="like_button_5241958541"><iframe id="like_iframe_5241958541" src="http://assets.tumblr.com/assets/html/like_iframe.html?_v=5716f9145cbbcc5e21aa13229de5d4ed#name=learninghindi&amp;post_id=5241958541&amp;color=grey&amp;rk=9Hwe8rXl" scrolling="no" width="16" height="16" frameborder="0" class="like_toggle" allowTransparency="true" name="like_iframe_5241958541"></iframe></div><a href="https://www.tumblr.com/reblog/5241958541/9Hwe8rXl" class="reblog_button"style="display: block;width:16px;height:16px;"><svg width="100%" height="100%" viewBox="0 0 21 21" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" fill="#ccc"><path d="M5.01092527,5.99908429 L16.0088498,5.99908429 L16.136,9.508 L20.836,4.752 L16.136,0.083 L16.1360004,3.01110845 L2.09985349,3.01110845 C1.50585349,3.01110845 0.979248041,3.44726568 0.979248041,4.45007306 L0.979248041,10.9999998 L3.98376463,8.30993634 L3.98376463,6.89801007 C3.98376463,6.20867902 4.71892527,5.99908429 5.01092527,5.99908429 Z"></path><path d="M17.1420002,13.2800293 C17.1420002,13.5720293 17.022957,14.0490723 16.730957,14.0490723 L4.92919922,14.0490723 L4.92919922,11 L0.5,15.806 L4.92919922,20.5103758 L5.00469971,16.9990234 L18.9700928,16.9990234 C19.56409